HEADWORD: Lumachella
<hw>Lu`ma*chel"la</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>lumachelle</ets>, It.
<ets>lumachella</ets>, fr. <ets>lamachella</ets> a little snail, dim. of
<ets>lumaca</ets> a snail, fr. L. <ets>limax</ets>,
<ets>-acis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A grayish brown
limestone, containing fossil shells, which reflect a beautiful play of
colors. It is also called <altname>fire marble</altname>, from its fiery
reflections.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lumbaginous</ent>⟦br⟧
